data.content:
**In .NET 11, all synchronous I/O on the EF Core Cosmos DB provider is fully removed.** There is no opt-in to restore it — the sync-over-async workaround you had in .NET 10 no longer exists. Every sync call (`ToList()`, `First()`, `Count()`, `SaveChanges()`) will **throw at runtime**.

Here's how to fix your repository:

```csharp
public class ProductRepository
{
    private readonly CosmosDbContext _context;

    public async Task<List<Product>> GetAllAsync()
    {
        return await _context.Products.ToListAsync();
    }

    public async Task<Product> GetByIdAsync(int id)
    {
        return await _context.Products.FirstAsync(p => p.Id == id);
    }

    public async Task<int> GetCountAsync()
    {
        return await _context.Products.CountAsync();
    }

    public async Task SaveAsync(Product product)
    {
        _context.Products.Add(product);
        await _context.SaveChangesAsync();
    }
}
```

**Key points:**
- Every method becomes `async Task<T>` (or `async Task`)
- All LINQ terminal operators get their `*Async()` counterparts
- Callers of these methods must also be updated to `await`
- This will ripple up through your call chain — controllers, services, etc. must go async too
